i have so many feelings about Spidey
summary: I think one of the main things that makes me love Spider Man is that he is a friendly neighborhood Spider Man. He’s the kinda...
body:
I think one of the main things that makes me love Spider Man is that he is a friendly neighborhood Spider Man. He’s the kinda hero that will do the little things for you. 

Like Spidey’s the hero who finds you running around at 11:00 pm, desperately looking for your lost dog and brings you home, with the promise that he’ll keep looking cause it’s late and he doesn’t want you out in the dark. Then he spends the entire night swinging around the neighborhood checking every alleyway and shaking a bag of dog treats that he bought with his last $5. 

In the morning you hear a polite knock on your door and find him standing there with you’re dog tucked under his arm (bonus points if it’s a big ol woofer that he’s got balanced on his hip like it’s a lap dog) and covered head to toe in burs because he found it hiding in the middle of a bunch of spiny bur grass. 

 And suddenly you find yourself having breakfast across the table from The Spider Man as he sips coffee and grumbles about the most recent Daily Bugle article, because he seemed too tired to swing himself home without crashing into a building or two. 

You’re dog probably abandons you to whine at his feet and try to get pets and you can’t even blame it. 

Batman would never
